explanation: This solution uses the `indexOf` method to find the first occurrence of the character `ch` in the string `word`. If the character is found, it uses a `StringBuilder` to reverse the substring from the start of the string to the index of the character, and then concatenates the rest of the string. If the character is not found, it simply returns the original string. The time complexity is O(n) because `indexOf` and `substring` operations take linear time, and the space complexity is O(n) because of the `StringBuilder` object.

